THE case against Springboks rugby player, Elton Jantjies,
for allegedly acting in an unruly manner on a flight from Turkey, was
provisionally withdrawn at the Kempton Park Magistrates’ Court on Friday 17
June 2022. Jantjies was charged with malicious injury to property and
Contravention of the Aviation Act. The case was set down for the outcome of representations he
lodged with the Senior Public Prosecutor of Kempton Park and after careful consideration,
the prosecution decided to provisionally withdraw his prosecution pending
confirmation of payment for damages caused to the plane, as per undertaking
from Jantjies. NPA spokeswoman, Phindi Mjonodwana said in statement, “The
prosecution will continue to engage with the complainant (Emirates Airline) to
ensure that the accused delivers on his undertaking. READ: Elton Jantjies case postponed! Jantjies was arrested when the plane landed at OR Tambo
International Airport, following complaints from the flight crew members about
a passenger in business class that was swearing at passengers and crew members.
He is also alleged to have broken a TV screen and bulb, when he was ordered to
return to his seat after breaking a glass that cut his finger, in the business
class stretching area.